### ==========================================================
### Challenge Service — 6 requests
### Flow: create challenge → list → view detail → claim/cancel
### Prerequisites: users must be friends, habit must exist
### ==========================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5050
@accessToken = <paste-after-login>
@habitId = <paste-habit-guid>
@friendId = <paste-friend-guid>
@challengeId = <paste-challenge-guid>

### 1. Create challenge (consistencyTarget)
# Valid milestoneType values: consistencyTarget, daysInPeriod,
#   totalCompletions, customDateRange, improvementMilestone
POST {{baseUrl}}/challenges
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "habitId": "{{habitId}}",
  "recipientId": "{{friendId}}",
  "milestoneType": "consistencyTarget",
  "targetValue": 80,
  "periodDays": 30,
  "rewardDescription": "Coffee at Starbucks"
}

### 2. Create challenge (daysInPeriod)
POST {{baseUrl}}/challenges
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "habitId": "{{habitId}}",
  "recipientId": "{{friendId}}",
  "milestoneType": "daysInPeriod",
  "targetValue": 20,
  "periodDays": 30,
  "rewardDescription": "Movie night"
}

### 3. List challenges (paginated)
# Response: { items: [...], page, pageSize, total }
# Items use detail shape: includes progress, completionCount, baselineConsistency
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges?page=1&pageSize=10
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3b. List challenges (filtered by status)
# Valid status values: active, completed, claimed, cancelled, expired
# Note: "expired" only returns DB-level expired, not virtually-expired active challenges
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges?page=1&pageSize=10&status=completed
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 3c. List challenges (updated since timestamp)
# Returns challenges updated after the given ISO 8601 timestamp
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges?page=1&pageSize=10&since=2026-03-01T00:00:00Z
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Get challenge detail (includes progress)
GET {{baseUrl}}/challenges/{{challengeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Claim completed challenge
PUT {{baseUrl}}/challenges/{{challengeId}}/claim
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 6. Cancel challenge (DESTRUCTIVE — run last)
# Only the creator can cancel; cannot cancel completed/claimed challenges
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/challenges/{{challengeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
